responses.description: The UTC date and time when someone created the ad. This is not the same as when someone first ran the ad. Includes date and time separated by T. Example: 2019-01-24T19:02:04+0000, where +0000 is the UTC offset.
responses.name: Ad Creation Time

responses.description: The text which displays in the ad. Typically 90 characters. See Reference, Ad Creative.
responses.name: Ad Creative Body

responses.description: If an ad contains a link, the text that appears in the link.
responses.name: Ad Creative Link Caption

responses.description: If an ad contains a link, any text description that appears next to the link, such as a caption or description.
responses.name: Ad Creative Link Description

responses.description: If an ad contains a link, any title provided.
responses.name: Ad Creative Link Title

responses.description: Date an time when an advertiser wants Facebook to start delivering an of the ad. Provided in UTC as in ad_creation_time.
responses.name: Ad Delivery Start Time

responses.description: The time when an advertiser wants to stop delivery of their ad. If this is blank, Facebook runs the ad until the advertiser stops it or they spend their entire campaign budget. In UTC.
responses.name: Ad Delivery Stop Time

responses.description: String with URL link which displays a rendered ad that Facebook saves. This displays uncompressed images and videos shown in the ad.
responses.name: Ad Snapshot Url

responses.description: A string containing the currency used to pay for the ad, as an ISO currency code
responses.name: Currency

responses.description: A string containing the name of the person, company, or entity that provided funding for the ad. As submitted by the purchaser of the ad.
responses.name: Funding Entity

responses.description: A numeric string containing the ID of the Facebook Page which ran the ad.
responses.name: Page Id

responses.description: A string containing the name of the Facebook Page which ran the ad.
responses.name: Page Name
